So I'll talk through
fennel overall.

00:15:04.810 --> 00:15:08.970
So this recipe is appearing
in the cantaloupe section,

00:15:08.970 --> 00:15:12.470
but it could just as well
appear in the purslane section.

00:15:12.470 --> 00:15:14.990
There actually really
isn't a purslane section,

00:15:14.990 --> 00:15:17.240
but purslane does appear
in the book a lot.

00:15:17.240 --> 00:15:20.184
Because I've got
one waiter who's

00:15:20.184 --> 00:15:21.600
been with me very,
very long time,

00:15:21.600 --> 00:15:24.214
who grows a lot
of purslane, Paul.

00:15:24.214 --> 00:15:24.880
AUDIENCE: Paul--

00:15:27.850 --> 00:15:29.600
HUGH ACHESON: So we're
going to take these

00:15:29.600 --> 00:15:33.410
and we're going to use half of
them in the beautiful salad,

00:15:33.410 --> 00:15:36.060
and half of them are
going to get pureed.

00:15:36.060 --> 00:15:37.820
So this is the
mortem moment that we

00:15:37.820 --> 00:15:40.665
cull the population
for the beautiful ones,

00:15:40.665 --> 00:15:43.650
and they stay out, and the
other one gets blended up.

00:15:43.650 --> 00:15:46.200
It's very strange totalitarian
regime of cooking.

00:15:48.980 --> 00:15:51.800
That's going in there.

00:15:51.800 --> 00:15:55.250
And then some
vinegar is going in.

00:15:55.250 --> 00:15:56.620
So if you make a vinaigrette.

00:15:56.620 --> 00:15:57.494
What's a vinaigrette?

00:15:57.494 --> 00:15:59.440
Vinaigrette is a
ratio, it's 3:1.

00:15:59.440 --> 00:16:00.230
Three to one what?

00:16:00.230 --> 00:16:06.580
Well, three to one oils,
and often olive oil,

00:16:06.580 --> 00:16:08.650
but it could be safflower
oil, or sunflower oil,

00:16:08.650 --> 00:16:11.150
or a salad oil, depending
on what type of flavors

00:16:11.150 --> 00:16:12.680
you want to bring to it.

00:16:12.680 --> 00:16:14.872
And then the one, is
the vinegar or acid.

00:16:14.872 --> 00:16:16.830
So that could be a
combination of citrus juices

00:16:16.830 --> 00:16:18.060
or any vinegars.

00:16:18.060 --> 00:16:20.170
And the balance is the
most basic vinaigrette

00:16:20.170 --> 00:16:21.410
you'll ever make.

00:16:21.410 --> 00:16:23.117
As you add other
things like the onions,

00:16:23.117 --> 00:16:24.700
you're not really
changing that ratio,

00:16:24.700 --> 00:16:27.300
you're just adding more
flavor components to it.

00:16:27.300 --> 00:16:29.800
So with simple
ratios like that, you

00:16:29.800 --> 00:16:32.157
can make life much
more convenient

00:16:32.157 --> 00:16:34.740
because you've now just avoided
an entire aisle in the grocery

00:16:34.740 --> 00:16:36.170
store.

00:16:36.170 --> 00:16:38.340
So that's the way
cooking from scratch

00:16:38.340 --> 00:16:41.690
should work and make
you think about things.

00:16:41.690 --> 00:16:46.260
I have two kids,
Beatrice is 13 now,

00:16:46.260 --> 00:16:48.660
but when she went off to
kindergarten when she was five,

00:16:48.660 --> 00:16:50.660
I remember hearing this
kerfuffle in the kitchen

00:16:50.660 --> 00:16:52.250
at 6 o'clock in the morning.

00:16:52.250 --> 00:16:57.134
And she was making a
vinaigrette in a Mason jar.

00:16:57.134 --> 00:16:58.800
Because that's how
we make them at home,

00:16:58.800 --> 00:17:01.008
is just put everything into
a mason jar and shake it.

00:17:01.008 --> 00:17:02.510
And she had made
this salad to go,

00:17:02.510 --> 00:17:05.210
and she's standing on her
stool, making all this stuff

00:17:05.210 --> 00:17:07.543
and it's 6 o'clock in the
morning, she's climbing around

00:17:07.543 --> 00:17:08.560
and made a mess.

00:17:08.560 --> 00:17:12.450
But for you, she made her
own stuff to go to school,

00:17:12.450 --> 00:17:14.930
now she's like uh-nun,
because she's 13

00:17:14.930 --> 00:17:17.500
and that's what they do.

00:17:17.500 --> 00:17:20.450
I'm going to add a little
bit of salt to this,

00:17:20.450 --> 00:17:22.482
and then we're going
to start pureeing.

00:17:30.110 --> 00:17:32.860
Basically, in the
emulsification process

00:17:32.860 --> 00:17:36.020
you want to add this in
relatively thin, or slowly.

00:17:36.020 --> 00:17:37.520
If you add it in
really slow, you're

00:17:37.520 --> 00:17:40.960
going to make a
onion mayonnaise,

00:17:40.960 --> 00:17:44.432
so don't go too slowly.

00:17:44.432 --> 00:17:46.390
And if you need to balance
the thickness of it,

00:17:46.390 --> 00:17:48.240
you can stop and
add more vinegar.

00:17:48.240 --> 00:17:50.020
You can also thin with water.

00:17:50.020 --> 00:17:52.475
[BLENDER MOTOR]

00:18:16.470 --> 00:18:20.340
HUGH ACHESON: And don't
be afraid to taste things

00:18:20.340 --> 00:18:22.260
as you're going along.

00:18:22.260 --> 00:18:24.504
This looks compostable?

00:18:24.504 --> 00:18:26.090
Nice.

00:18:26.090 --> 00:18:28.900
You guys, as a uniform
team, you're like yes.

00:18:28.900 --> 00:18:31.750
Go green.

00:18:31.750 --> 00:18:34.760
So that is pretty much
done, the end result

00:18:34.760 --> 00:18:36.900
is looking like this.

00:18:36.900 --> 00:18:39.020
We just made a really
simple vinaigrette

00:18:39.020 --> 00:18:42.760
in a matter of moments and it's
really not that hard to do.

00:18:42.760 --> 00:18:44.950
Because it's got that
roasted allium flavor, which

00:18:44.950 --> 00:18:47.660
is the onion, it's really
got a ton of flavor to it,

00:18:47.660 --> 00:18:48.760
so it's pretty versatile.

00:18:48.760 --> 00:18:51.210
It'll keep in the fridge,
for five, six seven days.

00:18:51.210 --> 00:18:52.668
There's not really
much perishable,

00:18:52.668 --> 00:18:55.310
other than the butter and the
onion that was cooked in there,

00:18:55.310 --> 00:18:57.030
so the other things-- I
mean obviously the oil

00:18:57.030 --> 00:18:58.946
is perishable, but it
takes a much longer time

00:18:58.946 --> 00:19:01.170
for that to go to a bad point.

00:19:01.170 --> 00:19:04.030
So when we say it'll say good,
it'll stay good in the fridge

00:19:04.030 --> 00:19:05.690
obviously.

00:19:05.690 --> 00:19:07.454
So let's take all the
other elements to it

00:19:07.454 --> 00:19:09.620
and lay them aside, and
we'll build our salad later.

00:19:09.620 --> 00:19:12.510
And let's go through
right now and we'll just

00:19:12.510 --> 00:19:17.490
start the other elements
for the fennel salad.

