We're just going to throw this
in with the-- it'll probably

00:19:42.722 --> 00:19:44.270
be a good time.

00:19:44.270 --> 00:19:45.792
How are you?

00:19:45.792 --> 00:19:48.580
You're doing pretty good.

00:19:48.580 --> 00:19:50.910
Here we go.

00:19:50.910 --> 00:19:53.250
And it's got anchovies it in.

00:19:53.250 --> 00:19:55.450
Usually they would be
Spanish white anchovies.

00:19:55.450 --> 00:19:58.580
These are Italian salted
anchovies, which are flat guys,

00:19:58.580 --> 00:20:00.710
so we're just going to
rinse them quite well, quite

00:20:00.710 --> 00:20:02.294
aggressively in cold water.

00:20:02.294 --> 00:20:03.960
And then pat them dry
and then fold them

00:20:03.960 --> 00:20:06.470
into a salad at the end.

00:20:06.470 --> 00:20:10.630
In this, we're going to shave
the fennel by cutting off

00:20:10.630 --> 00:20:12.380
the main bulb part.

00:20:12.380 --> 00:20:15.260
We're going to cut in
half and lightly core it.

00:20:15.260 --> 00:20:17.030
So I'm going to-- and
then we're going--

00:20:17.030 --> 00:20:19.130
I saved some of the frond.

