So it you had other
things in-- I'm just

00:29:01.320 --> 00:29:06.050
trying to take the blinders off
and expand the horizons of what

00:29:06.050 --> 00:29:09.610
you're thinking about-- is
cooking at home with food

00:29:09.610 --> 00:29:14.120
and also making you realize it's
really not as difficult as most

00:29:14.120 --> 00:29:15.455
people make it seem.

00:29:18.067 --> 00:29:20.150
We have a vested interest
in you guys still coming

00:29:20.150 --> 00:29:22.250
to restaurants
obviously, because it's

00:29:22.250 --> 00:29:24.520
how I pay my mortgage.

00:29:24.520 --> 00:29:28.100
But I want you to
cook at home, I

00:29:28.100 --> 00:29:31.000
want you to realize
that cooking is easy,

00:29:31.000 --> 00:29:33.449
but I don't know-- none
of you probably have kids,

00:29:33.449 --> 00:29:34.240
you're tech people.

00:29:37.222 --> 00:29:38.930
FEMALE SPEAKER: How
many of us have kids?

00:29:38.930 --> 00:29:41.263
HUGH ACHESON: How many of
you-- do you have kids-- Nice.

00:29:41.263 --> 00:29:42.250
Nice.

00:29:42.250 --> 00:29:43.450
AUDIENCE: Grandkids.

00:29:43.450 --> 00:29:45.200
HUGH ACHESON: You know,
I mean, grandkids?

00:29:45.200 --> 00:29:46.574
That's awesome,
what are you, 40?

00:29:46.574 --> 00:29:49.135
[LAUGHTER]

00:29:49.135 --> 00:29:51.010
HUGH ACHESON: I think
the important thing is,

00:29:51.010 --> 00:29:53.270
the best time you'll ever
have in your life if you

00:29:53.270 --> 00:29:55.360
are a parent is
cooking with your kids,

00:29:55.360 --> 00:29:56.410
because it's multi-fold.

00:29:56.410 --> 00:29:58.210
You're teaching
them life skills.

00:29:58.210 --> 00:30:01.050
Because at 20 years old,
you remember, all remember,

00:30:01.050 --> 00:30:02.240
how hard it was.

00:30:02.240 --> 00:30:04.900
You're on your own,
you're eating crappy food,

00:30:04.900 --> 00:30:08.400
you miss the Happy Meal, but
they won't sell to you anymore.

00:30:08.400 --> 00:30:11.570
This idea of how to feed
ourselves, and life skills,

00:30:11.570 --> 00:30:15.120
and surround ourselves with
basic cooking things, this food

00:30:15.120 --> 00:30:18.260
is not expensive to make at all.

00:30:18.260 --> 00:30:22.940
But it's good food and if I can
teach my kids, like Beatrice,

00:30:22.940 --> 00:30:26.549
again shaking it, at five
years old making vinaigrette.

00:30:26.549 --> 00:30:28.590
If I could teach her also
how to scramble an egg,

00:30:28.590 --> 00:30:31.050
and make a perfect omelette,
and make a simple soup,

00:30:31.050 --> 00:30:34.590
and roasted chicken, I'm done.

00:30:34.590 --> 00:30:37.890
I gave her enough that she can
feed her and her six friends,

00:30:37.890 --> 00:30:41.429
or her and her three families if
she starts having babies soon,

00:30:41.429 --> 00:30:43.220
she's going to be in
deep shit if she does.

00:30:45.780 --> 00:30:48.330
But this is the idea.

00:30:48.330 --> 00:30:51.350
To me, I live in a
community, it ain't my kids,

00:30:51.350 --> 00:30:53.540
it's everybody's kids
who are around me,

00:30:53.540 --> 00:30:55.830
and if you then take
the circles of community

00:30:55.830 --> 00:30:58.080
and make them bigger,
it's everywhere.

00:30:58.080 --> 00:31:01.830
We've got a duty to make sure
that the next generation has

00:31:01.830 --> 00:31:04.770
much more endowed life
skills than we do.

00:31:04.770 --> 00:31:06.810
So that's the important thing.

00:31:06.810 --> 00:31:10.370
Let's plate up this other one.

00:31:10.370 --> 00:31:13.660
This is again beautiful--
the beautiful onions,

00:31:13.660 --> 00:31:15.600
this is the prosciutto,
so I'm going

00:31:15.600 --> 00:31:17.400
to get a little
bit of that down,

00:31:17.400 --> 00:31:21.720
and I'm going to take some of
my purslane and my vinaigrette.

00:31:21.720 --> 00:31:24.010
I'm going to just put the
dressing on at the very top,

00:31:24.010 --> 00:31:27.460
because I don't want to wilt
this purslane down too much.

00:31:27.460 --> 00:31:31.530
And then the onions go
in, and I'm just going

00:31:31.530 --> 00:31:36.254
to layer another bit of this.

00:31:36.254 --> 00:31:38.420
This is pretty-- you don't
have to have a fancy meat

00:31:38.420 --> 00:31:40.440
slicer at home.

00:31:40.440 --> 00:31:43.890
There's batting cage
though, out back,

